§ 1. GStreamer
--------------

Used by:        `plugin/` (the macttssink GStreamer element links against
                the GStreamer 1.x runtime via Meson/pkg-config).
Distribution:   The GStreamer runtime is NOT vendored inside this source
                tree. End users install it from the official package below.
                When a `.app` release is produced via PyInstaller, parts of
                the GStreamer runtime may be bundled inside the `.app`.
License:        LGPL-2.1-or-later (core / base / good libraries).
                Individual plugins outside the core set may carry other
                licenses; consult each plugin's own license notice.
Source:         The corresponding source code is available from the
                upstream project at
                https://gstreamer.freedesktop.org/src/
                and via the official downloads page at
                https://gstreamer.freedesktop.org/download/ .
LGPL compliance: Because this is dynamic linking against an LGPL library,
                end users are entitled to replace the GStreamer runtime
                with their own modified version. Installing a different
                version of the official GStreamer Framework or pointing
                `DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH` / `GST_PLUGIN_PATH` at a custom build
                is sufficient for this purpose.


§ 2. PySide6 / Qt
-----------------

Used by:        `gui/` (the PySide6 desktop application). Both PySide6
                (Python bindings) and the underlying Qt 6 libraries are
                installed into the virtual environment via PyPI and are
                bundled into the final `.app` release by PyInstaller.
License:        Qt for Python (PySide6) and Qt are offered under multiple
                license options. K-Balabolka uses them under the terms of
                the GNU Lesser General Public License version 3
                (LGPL-3.0-only).
                The full multi-option SPDX expression observed in the
                upstream sources is:
                  LicenseRef-Qt-Commercial OR LGPL-3.0-only
                  OR GPL-2.0-only OR GPL-3.0-only
Source:         PySide6 source distributions:
                  https://pypi.org/project/PySide6/#files
                Qt source archives:
                  https://download.qt.io/official_releases/qt/
LGPL compliance: PySide6 and Qt are loaded as dynamic libraries inside the
                `.app` bundle, so end users may replace them with a
                compatible version of their own. `gui/requirements.txt`
                records only a lower bound (`PySide6>=6.8`); the exact
                version included in a particular `.app` release is the
                version resolved by pip at build time. It can be inspected
                from the PyInstaller build log, or by reading the bundled
                `PySide6/__init__.py` (look for `__version__`) inside the
                released `.app`.


